        <body>       
                                
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>4045 Ellis avenue<lb/>
                Chicago May 19&#45;&#45;92.<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Mr Mora&#239;s<lb/></p>
            <p>Let me from<lb/> the bottom of my heart<lb/> thank you for your<lb/> kindness to me&#44; away from<lb/> Philadelphia at a time<lb/> when I would like<lb/> personally to put a<lb/> child&#39;s blessing on my<lb/> poor father&#39;s grave&#44;<lb/> you took away from<lb/> me all my regrets<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>for your benediction<lb/> is so sacred in my eyes&#44;<lb/> that it seems papa<lb/> forever will have a<lb/> peace &#38; rest.  God<lb/> will surely bless his<lb/> soul.  It was such a<lb/> great satisfaction to me.<lb/></p>
            <p>I have the<lb/> pleasure to see dear<lb/> Nina but only a<lb/> glimpse as her time here<lb/> was so limited &#38;<lb/> taken that I could<lb/> only see her a few<lb/> minutes to my sorrow.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>She looks splendid<lb/> always the dear grand<lb/> girl of old.<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear husband<lb/> just returned from a<lb/> trip&#44; wishes me to send<lb/> you his heartiest<lb/> greetings.  Graziella is a<lb/> wonderful child and<lb/> will some day make<lb/> a mark in the world.<lb/></p>
            <p>I am pretty<lb/> well&#44; much stronger<lb/> than the years past<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="4"/>
            <p>and hope God will<lb/> spare me new sorrow<lb/> &#38; illnesses.<lb/></p>
            <p>Adieu&#44; my noble<lb/> friend.  God guard<lb/> you.  I take your<lb/> hands in mine and a<lb/> warm handshaking<lb/> tells you once more<lb/> Merci.<lb/></p>
            <p>Your affectionate<lb/> young friend<lb/> Hermine Jacoby<lb/></p>
            </body>
